Replaces the actual value in the option by the value given in parameter,
returning the old value if present,
leaving a [`Some`] in its place without deinitializing either one.

# Examples

```
let mut x = Some(2);
let old = x.replace(5);
assert_eq!(x, Some(5));
assert_eq!(old, Some(2));

let mut x = None;
let old = x.replace(3);
assert_eq!(x, Some(3));
assert_eq!(old, None);
```
